$Id: README,v 1.1 2003/01/07 21:03:40 eric Exp $

--------
Abstract
--------

XML::Filter::PerlTidy is a SAX filter It pipes character data within
a given element of the source XML document into the Perl::Tidy module,
and reinjects that module's output into the SAX stream. Perl::Tidy
produces pretty syntax colored HTML from Perl code.

------------
Requirements
------------

This module requires XML::SAX.

------------------
Basic Installation
------------------

XML::Filter::PerlTidy may be installed through the CPAN shell in the
usual manner:

  # perl -MCPAN -e 'install XML::Filter::PerlTidy'

You can also read this README from the CPAN shell:

  # perl -MCPAN -e shell
  cpan> readme XML::Filter::PerlTidy

And you can install the component from the CPAN prompt as well:

  cpan> install XML::Filter::PerlTidy

-------------------
Manual Installation
-------------------

XML::Filter::PerlTidy can also be installed manually.  The latest CPAN
version can be found at
<http://www.cpan.org/modules/by-authors/id/C/CH/CHOLET/> or in a
similarly named directory at your favorite CPAN mirror.

Downloading and unpacking the distribution are left as exercises for
the reader.  To build and test it:

  perl Makefile.PL
  make test

When you're ready to install the component:

  make install

It should now be ready to use.

On Win32 systems, replace "make" in the above commands with "nmake".
The nmake utility can be downloaded from
C<http://download.microsoft.com/download/vc15/Patch/1.52/W95/EN-US/Nmake15.exe>
